On my Ubuntu 18 its size it 
about 10MB. Bumping up the number of lines, 
and thereby bumping up the size, is easy. 
Just increase the head -n 100000 part. So, say, this command:














tr -dc "A-Za-z 0-9" < /dev/urandom | fold -w100|head -n 1000000 > bigfile.txt
will generate a file with 1,000,000 of random lines of text and be around 100MB.
On my commodity hardware the latter command takes about 3 seconds to finish.







Linux users
Arbitrarily large text files can be generated on 
Linux with the following command:

tr -dc "A-Za-z 0-9" < /dev/urandom | fold -w100|head -n 100000 > bigfile.txt
This command will generate a text file that will 
contain 100,000 lines of random text and look like this:




5000 in words is written as Five thousand. The number 5000 tells the count of objects or anything countable; hence it is a counting number. The numeral 5000 represents a value that is used in Maths and in real-life in many different ways. For example, while writing 5000 rupees in a cheque, we can write Five-thousand only or Rupees Five thousand only. By this example, we can understand how important it is to learn the numbers in words in the primary classes. Let us see in this article how to write 5000 in words.

5000 in words	Five Thousand
Five Thousand in Numbers	5000
How to Convert 5000 in words?
To write a number into words, we should have knowledge of the place value of the digits in the number. The right-most digit in a number is said to be at units place or ones place. The rest of the positions are learned from right to left in a number, in an order of:

Ones
Tens
Hundreds
Thousands
Ten-thousands
Hundred-thousands or Lakhs
Thus, we can write the number 5000 in words using the place value method.

5	0	0	0
Thousands	Hundreds	Tens	Ones
From the above table, we can say, 5 is at thousands place.

Hence,

5 x 1000 = 5000

Therefore, 5000 is written as Five thousand in words.

To understand in a better way, see the below table.

5	000
Five	Thousand
5000 in English
English is the most common language used worldwide for education. Hence, it is necessary to learn the numbers also in English. The spelling of 5000 in English is Five thousand.

What is 5000?
In Maths, 5000 is a numeral that expresses a value or a count. The numeral 5000 is written as Five thousand in words. Other specifications of the number 5000 are:

5000 is a cardinal number
5000 is an even number
5000 is a natural number
5000 is a whole number
5000 is a composite number
